      <h2>How It Works</h2>
      <p>
        Eight GitHub organizations, each representing a distinct organ with a Greek ontological suffix.<Cite id={3} author="Alexander, Christopher" title="A Pattern Language: Towns, Buildings, Construction" source="Oxford University Press" year={1977} /> Alexander's "pattern language" proposes that environments are shaped by named, interrelating patterns — here, each organ is a named pattern governing a domain of creative practice. The naming is not decorative: Greek ontological terms encode the organ's epistemological function.<Cite id={4} author="Meadows, Donella H." title="Thinking in Systems: A Primer" source="Chelsea Green Publishing" year={2008} />
      </p>

